{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c474d0b4-9840-439b-9144-6cda6055aabc","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped** (not failed) in test results, with your reason message visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5d228d45-50e7-462a-a6e6-0d24506b26d3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question - no tools needed.","outputTokens":304,"requestId":"4C3C:B4CFF:E09422:116BC40:6A012D80"},"id":"00cd499e-bfbd-4a4f-822e-1a4fb2b6bd1b","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:14:47.204Z","parentId":"ef025f7d-bfa2-4f83-9840-8620564ca99f"}
